               <msContents>
                  <summary>Theodoros, a brother of Amyntas, writes to say that, having found Python, the well-known banker, at Athribis, he had received from him the sum of one thousand drachmae.  He also asks Zenon to deliver, at a propitious moment, a letter from Amyntas to Apollonios about Python and to see that an order is written about the payment of his salary.</summary>
